#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Troubleshooting Prompts"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"Creating prompts is a straightforward process and you will seldom run into "
"any difficulties. However, there are a few situations within which your "
"prompts may need to be slightly reconfigured for best results. There are "
"also situations within which it is necessary to create your prompts in a "
"specific manner. Several of these situations are listed below with our "
"recommendations for how to make your prompts work best."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid "A prompt is Recognized in Several Dialogs"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.p:20-1"
msgid "Prompts in Multipage Dialogs"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:21-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.p:21-1"
msgid "A Prompt that does not Size to the Control"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:22-1
msgid "A Prompt is Recognized in Several Dialogs"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:23-1
msgid ""
"It is possible FOR a prompt to be recognized within several dialogs within "
"the same application. This can only occur when the dialogs in an application "
"use similar names and the controls in them are laid out similarly."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:24-1
msgid ""
"When prompts are created, the text from the title of the dialog in which the "
"control is located is recorded. The prompt is then available whenever a "
"dialog in that application containing that text is opened. Because of this, "
"if you create a prompt in a dialog titled \"Options,\" and that same "
"application also has a dialog named \"Format Options\" or something else "
"containing the word \"options,\" the prompt is recognized in that dialog as "
"well. And if there is a control in that dialog in the same position as that "
"for which you created the prompt, the prompt is spoken when you <b>TAB</b> "
"to that control."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid "To correct this:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:27-1
msgid "Open the dialog where you created the prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:28-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:28-1"
msgid ""
"Press <b>INSERT+F2</b> to open the Run JAWS Manager dialog, select Frame "
"Viewer, and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:29-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:29-1"
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the frame with the name of your "
"prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:30-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:30-1"
msgid "Press <b>ALT+ENTER</b> to open properties for the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:31-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:31-1"
msgid ""
"Press <b>CTRL+TAB</b> to move to the Validation Rules page of this dialog."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-1
msgid "Select the Window Title rule and press <b>ALT+M</b> to modify it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:33-1
msgid "Do not change the rule type. Move to Next and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:34-1
msgid "Change the comparison type from Contains to Is and select Next."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:35-1
msgid "Do not change the comparison value. Select Finish."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:36-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:36-1"
msgid ""
"You should be back in the Validation Rules page of properties. Press "
"<b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:37-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:37-1"
msgid "Press <b>CTRL+S</b> to save changes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:38-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:38-1"
msgid "Press <b>ESC</b> to exit Frame Viewer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:40-1
msgid ""
"Your prompt should now work only in the dialog for which it was intended."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:41-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.h2:41-1"
msgid "Prompts in Multipage Dialogs"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:42-1
msgid ""
"Prompts created within multipage dialogs may be recognized within several "
"pages of the dialog. This is because the title of the dialog is used to "
"determine when the prompt is available, and the title of multipage dialogs "
"do not change as you move from page to page."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:43-1
msgid ""
"To prevent this, the prompt must look for something unique in the page of "
"the dialog where it was created. We recommend identifying text of some sort "
"within the page, which is not present in any other pages of the dialog. Once "
"you have identified such text, follow these steps to set your prompt to only "
"be available when that text is present."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:45-1
msgid "Open the dialog to the page where you created the prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:46-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:46-1"
msgid ""
"Press <b>INSERT+F2</b> to open the Run JAWS Manager dialog, select Frame "
"Viewer, and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:47-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:47-1"
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the frame with the name of your "
"prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:48-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:48-1"
msgid "Press <b>ALT+ENTER</b> to open properties for the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:49-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:49-1"
msgid ""
"Press <b>CTRL+TAB</b> to move to the Validation Rules page of this dialog."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:50-1
msgid "Press <b>ALT+A</b> to modify a new rule."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:51-1
msgid "Set the rule type to Window Text. Move to Next and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:52-1
msgid "Leave the comparison type set to Contains, and select Next."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:53-1
msgid ""
"For the comparison value, type in the text you identified as unique to the "
"page of the dialog where you want your prompt to work. Press <b>TAB</b> to "
"move to the Add button and press <b>ENTER</b>. Then select Finish."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:54-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:54-1"
msgid ""
"You should be back in the Validation Rules page of properties. Press "
"<b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:55-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:55-1"
msgid "Press <b>CTRL+S</b> to save changes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:56-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.ol.li:56-1"
msgid "Press <b>ESC</b> to exit Frame Viewer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:58-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Troubleshooting_Prompts.htm+html.body.h2:58-1"
msgid "A Prompt that does not Size to the Control"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:59-1
msgid ""
"You may find situations where a prompt you create does not correctly size to "
"the control or area of the screen in which you want to use it. One example "
"of this is when creating prompts for use in terminal emulation software. In "
"these cases, it may be necessary to create the prompt in another manner."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:60-1
msgid ""
"You can use the JAWS cursor to specify the exact position of the top left "
"and bottom right corners of your prompt, limiting it to the exact area where "
"you need it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:62-1
msgid ""
"With the JAWS cursor, navigate to the top, left corner of the area you want "
"included in the prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:63-1
msgid "Press <b>CTRL+SHIFT+LEFT BRACKET</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:64-1
msgid ""
"Move to the bottom, right corner of the area you wish to include in the "
"prompt, and press <b>CTRL+SHIFT+RIGHT BRACKET</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:65-1
msgid ""
"A dialog box appears asking you if you wish to create a frame or a prompt. "
"Select to create a prompt."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CTroubleshooting_Prompts.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:67-1
msgid ""
"The standard Prompt Creator dialogs appear. Fill out the information on each "
"page just like with any other prompt."
msgstr ""

